text: Schouwen-Duiveland, Zeelandic: Schouwen-Duveland, is an island and municipality of the province of Zeeland, the Netherlands. In 2016 the municipality had about 34,000 people. The municipality covers an area of 488 km², the island an area of 230 km². == Other websites == * Category:Zeelandic Islands
